INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20170221141201', N'Challenge Decathlon & Greet Growth (2016 USAD Leadership Camp)', N'5', N'yumingmei', N'2017-02-21 14:10:00.0000000', N'["During the National Day holiday, Vanke Meisha Academy (VMA), the international high school jointly founded by Vanke Education Development Foundation and Shenzhen Middle School, welcomed some special guests. As the official academic partner of 2016 USAD China division, the training camp project of United States Academic Decathlon (USAD) China division was held by VMA. 58 junior high school and high school students and 22 freshmen of VMA actively took part in this training camp. As the host, VMA students treated guests warmly and courteously, they established friendship with their companions from other cities after learning and living together for 5 or 6 days, which was owed to their enthusiasm, generosity, and pioneering and innovation spirit. Thanks to these rich courses and lectures, participants of the camp got a chance to discuss and think about a series of questions about life philosophy and real-life significance, and thus learned new thinking methods and rules of getting along with others. Their careful listening and active discussion made a beautiful mark in their growth course.","As one of the top comprehensive academic competition platform that was founded 47 years ago for high school students in the U.S., USAD aims to help students display their knowledge and educational skills in 10 different academic categories. Therefore, the teaching materials of each subject are closely related to the theme released by USAD for the year and the curriculum issued by the country. The theme integrating seven subjects enables students to learn in a new perspective and through systematic thinking mode and accelerates their new academic interests. Consequently, students can improve their learning results in school, which will make them well prepared for university studies. In addition, each team comprises 9 students in the ninth grade and twelfth grade of the same school. They are divided into three academic levels: honor level, scholar level and varsity level; the two highest scores of the level, totally six scores will be recorded as the score of the team. This competition mechanism not only requires participants to improve themselves, but also work with the team. Besides, they have to be good at expressing and listening, to respect personality, different view and sounds and innovation.","The leadership camp of USAD China division consists of two parts, the SKT youth leadership transition camp in Oct.1-3 and USAD campus association core leadership camp in Oct.4 to 6. Although these two parts were focusing on different training content, both of them were aiming to strengthen students’ self-control and leadership and improve their comprehensive qualities, so that they will be able to attract the attention of USAD organizing committee and Ivy League. The youth leadership transition camp had Howard Chang, the former peace negotiator of UN Headquarters in New York and the current senior lecturer for senior strategic consultants of UNDP Great China area as its main lecturer. He guided students to rethink about individuals, interpersonal relationships and periodical losses and gains through meditation for horizon widening, self-discovery and responsibility cultivation.","Students also learned a lot from the USAD campus association core leadership camp that held in Oct. 4-6. Several trainers with rich overseas learning experiences and USAD competition instruction experiences motivated students with their humorous teaching content, fine lectures and feasible learning methods. After finishing all planned courses, Tan Ziying, a VMA freshman summarized her learning results like this: “The training tells me what is managed by these so-called management methods is not time but ourselves. Therefore, we should focus on efficiency management not just time management”. With the correct direction understood, they will renew their cognition about self-management.","In their remote video interactive with Steven, students discussed and learned about “India”, the USAD theme of 2016 by using the subject contest preparation methods they knew. With respect to the special subjects such as Arts, Math, Literature and Speech, Interview and Writing, Sound pronunciation, Linguistic organization, Listening and Speaking and body language training for students were organized during the course. Besides, literary and artistic works reading and evaluation, music and art appreciation, interview and speech and paper writing skills were supplemented in order to help students prepare with effective method and principle, establish team learning framework and methods, break through individual and team bottlenecks and realize the competition objective maximally at the end. Steven said this way: “The competition is established to make students learn these subjects as a whole so as to strengthen their task-taking skills. Meanwhile, students should learn how to organize a team and to play their roles in the team. USAD competition also aims to help students build up confidence in academic competitions and find their potentials.”","“The way you spend each day is the way you will live your whole life.” The academic level and ideological morality were expressed by students receiving training every moment at VMA. Their vitality, confidence, generosity, creativity and leadership will all put down on the road they will go in the future. In the 6-day USAD camp, two batches of VMA students played their master roles well. In the first day of training, students helped with reception when they saw students from other cities registering at the receptionist upon arrival: they led students to the classroom for activity from the entrance, and answered all questions. During class break, they took other students to buy beverages, filling water bottles or to the rest room. During lunch time, they helped lost students and parents to find the canteen. The things they did cannot be told in details, but they showed the elegant demeanor of VMA to students from Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Chengdu. We are waiting to see these youths with Chinese spirit heading in the way to world citizens and leaders shine the spirit of Meisha in a global context in future!"]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
GO
GO
