INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160128113601', N'Day 8: Never Say Goodbye', N'3', N'Admin', N'2016-02-01 16:01:23.0000000', N'["\n\t-Note\non the Eighth-day in 2015 Meisha Academy Orientation Camp\n","\n\n\tThe joyful time was always\nfleeting and here came the last night for this camp after just a “blink of eyes’.\nHowever, there’s not much leisure time for students even if the rich outdoor\nactivities experience and two-day camping as youth training plan were just\nfinished. More tasks were waiting for them today.\n","\n\n\tEarly in the\nmorning, all groups had begun their busy discussion, summarizing and rethinking\nabout the two-day experience and preparing PPT for report on the achievements.\nIn the afternoon, achievement report would be separately made in Madrid\nconference room and libratory by Group A and B, one group would be the winner\nto enter ultimate PK. The students were busy arranging photos, summarizing\nexperience and discussing about the self-introduction and display mode which\nwas full of creativity in order to show the best achievements to all.\n","\n\n\tThe tense preparation stage was ended\nfollowed by the formal reporting, in which, the students tried to show their\nideas about the two-day camping experience using novel words and pictures in a humorous\nway, but they had also prepared “real skills and knowledge” behind these\nwacky styles. Under the guidance of instructors, they had assembled a team from\nindividual strangers, entered forest under burning sun from comfortable house,\nbecome capable of identifying direction using compass and map from a kid who\ncould get lost, capable of lighting a fire for cooking from the “little emperor”, and become\npositive and enthusiastic from kids with publicizing individuality…each letter on\nPPT represented the real experience and feeling of students in the whole journey.\nAccording to final voting, A3 Monster and B4\nAwsome Potatos stood out to have the final PK.\n","\n\n\tIn the meantime,an evening party for\ncamp ending was prepared by a mysterious group, i.e. the director group, which\nhad received the task the day before yesterday and all resources they had were one\nempty stage, some microphones and basic light devices. All work including\nprogram planning, props preparation, game design, musical composition and program\nhost had to be completed by these students themselves. However, all\ndifficulties were solved by the students. The director group was quickly established\nby Group A and B to invite the students to prepare programs, review such\nprograms and urge the rehearsal and an excellent evening party was to come.\n","\n\n\tGood things were\nalways worthy of waiting. What was the excellence in the party of these\nstudents?\n","\n\n\tAt 19:30 on\nAugust 31, the breathtaking evening party for camp ending was formally started\nwith the debut of four hosts and the atmosphere lit up quickly. Under the\nenthusiastic cheers of students, the student from Group B4 came on the stage\nfirst to perform the Rice Field with\nmuch excellence, the perfect singing of six students won the applause of all students,\nafter which, the programs which were elaborately prepared by students who were\nput on stage in sequence, including the affectionate and touching song See You Again, dynamic double jazz\ndance, affectionate guitar playing, excellent magic show and exciting dance Little Apple…There were shining shadows\non stage and the laughing and applauses under stage; the versatility of students\nwere highly appraised by instructors and teachers on stage. At the ending of\nparty, the instructors and class teachers also gave excellent dancing, singing\nand band performance and the party had a perfect ending under the warm cheering\nof students.\n","\n\n\tThe students of\nMeisha Academy spent nine days in Twin Moon Bay, Huizhou, which were\nunforgettable to them and they would go ahead together in the incoming three\nyears. The every tree and brush had witnessed their hardworking, friendship and\ngrowth, and would become memory for their entire life. They would return to\nVankeMeisha Academy tomorrow to prepare for the new semester. The dream was\njust started, and the youth was on the sailing.May the youth struggle hard,\nclimb the high mountains, sail in the vast sea and become excellent!\n","\n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
GO
GO
INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160129164520', N'Make Unremitting Efforts with a Clear Destination', N'99', N'Admin', N'2016-01-29 16:45:55.0000000', N'["\n\tMake\nUnremitting Efforts with a Clear Destination \n","\n\n\t---VMA 2015-2016 Closing Ceremony\n","\n\n\tJanuary 28 is\nthe last day of 2015-2016 semester. Right after the tense final examination, it\ncame the first Vanke Meisha Academy (VMA) closing ceremony. We were glad to\nhave four students of Shenzhen Middle School (SMS) as our guests: Zhou Zixuan,\nCao Jining, and Wang Shangling brought their precious experience on preparation\nof college application; Zhou Qianzi lectured us a specific topic of detailed\nstrategies on TOEFL examination. All of the teachers and studenattended the\nceremony and benefited a lot. At last,in the wonderful wishes from Principal\nWang He, the first VMA closing ceremony concluded.\n","\n\n\tAfter the serious\nflag-rising ritual, it came the wonderful three lectures. The first lecture was\npresented by SMS 2015 graduates Cao Jining and Zhou Zixuan, sharing their\nsuccessful experience of college application. Cao Jining is now studying at\nEcole Hoteliere Lausanne，Switzerland\nand Zhou Zixuan is now a student of New York University. Their speech was\nmainly about “make a clear destination” and follow your interest to engage into\ninternships, co-curriculum activities, exchanges, and get to know the\nuniversities. They both suggest VMA students act earlier and start to discover\ntheir own interests and passion, then conduct research about the major,\nuniversities through the internet and mass media. Zhou Zixuan emphasized many\ntimes that the GPA is very important. They were so modest to confess that it\nwas a pity that they did not study hard at the first and second year of high\nschool, which resulted in the extremely tense accumulation of standard tests at\nthe last year. Their simple but sincere words made VMA students feel the power\nof good example and the time urgency to preparation for the standard tests.\n","\n\n\tThe second\nlecture was from Zhou Qianzi, who once achieved the high TOEFL score of 112.\nShe focused her speech on the TOEFL tests, especially the realistic learning\nstrategies at the first year of high school. At first, the goal should be set\nhigh: 100+ (more specific: Reading:27+，Listening:26+，Speaking:22+，Writing: 25+)，thus to relief the later stress. The second, student\nshould pay attention to these necessary materials: vocabulary book, TPO,\nPractice tests, and iBT TOEFL experiences. She also listed some learning\nmethods when referring to a particular area. For example, the reading part, she\nstrongly advice VMA students to recite a big amount of vocabulary and analyze\nevery difficult sentences, and go through the TPO reading during the first year\nof high school. She also gave suggestions on writing, speaking, and listening\nparts. The lecture by Zhou Qianzi brought VMA timely help, as they are on their\nway to try their first TOEFL test during the winter vacation. Therefore, all\nthe students took out paper and pen to record the important points raised by\nZhou Qianzi.， \n","\n\n\tThe third\nlecture was from SMS current student Wang Shangling, who has just received her\nearly offer from University of Chicago. As the same as what the previous two\nlectures referred, Wang Shangling proposed that VMA students should begin the\npreparation earlier. She tended to correct students’ impression on vacation and\npointed out that the vacation is not for hanging out, sleeping, or playing; it\nis for continuous study, for a whole plan for the coming semester, and for a\nprecious time to fulfill your learning objectives. Firstly, students should\nschedule all the test on their calendar to show their current or long-term\nchallenges. Among all the motivations, personal interest is the best accompany\nand triggers for success. She had been trying to apply the famous international\nsummer school in Stanford although failed again and again, but she never gave\nup. Her belief supported her a lot, as she said, “As long as you work hard, and\nbe persistent, we can approach the success step by step. It may not be now, but\nthe success will definitely be reached by us.” She then further proposed that\nstudents should grasp the opportunities of conducting individual study at home\nduring winter vacation： review the study of the last semester,\nmake up for the deficiency, and make everyday a new progress. Her mother Ms Hu\nalso gave advices for students’ parents: “Actually, we could do a lot for our\nkids: to monitor their study, to help with the planning, and to cooperate with\nthem. While, the most important thing is to communicate.” Through Wang\nShangling and her mother’s speeches, we firmly concluded that there are a lot\nefforts waiting for both students and parents to make on the way to success.\nParents should try and explore students’ interest, support them, help them,\nassist them when facing the difficulties, and accompany them to the destination\nof success step by step.\n","\n\n\t\nThrough the three special lectures for VMA students, Principal Wang He\nexpressed her meaningful wishes for VMA students: Make Unremitting Efforts with\na Clear Destination. She called on students to seize the opportunities of the\ncoming winter vacation to achieve three important things: to explore your\ninterest, passion and to set up your goal, specifically, the university and the\nmajor you would choose to apply; to make short-term and long-term plans and to\nstrive to accomplish that step by step; to cherish the wonderful moments of\nfamily time and contribute your love to your family, because this is what\nChinese spirits lies in.\n","\n\n\tIn 2015，we sowed the seeds of hope, and the\nharvest is abundant knowledge and great happiness. When the spring of 2016 is\napproaching, the first VMA semester is meeting its end successfully. We hope\nall the VMA students will make use the winter vacation, make progress day by\nday, and face any opportunities and challenges with the Meisha spirits in 2016!\n","\n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
GO
GO
INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'201703100854570', N'各国大学的录取要求', N'12', N'huchun', N'2017-03-10 08:54:00.0000000', N'["　　美国的大学和学院会全面的考虑学生的各方面条件来进行录取，而并不只是学生的学术成就。很多大学和学院都会用通用申请系统，或用它们自己特定的申请方式。申请要求通常包括：","l 两封主要学科老师的推荐信（数学、科学、外国语言、历史/社会科学、和英语）","l 个人陈述和补充文书","l 课外活动和个人简历","l 两门SAT学科考试","l 托福或者雅思考试","l 其它：个人特长，面试表现，艺术作品集，兴趣展示","　　申请英国的大学将用UCAS申请系统申请最多五所学校。申请要求通常包括：","l个人陈述（一定要突出自己在所选课程上的兴趣以及与该领域相关的活动）","l相关学科的AP成绩或者/和SAT学科成绩","澳大利亚，加拿大，和香港","　　澳大利亚、加拿大和香港的本科生录取有着相同的评估程序。大部分学校都有自己的申请表格。个别项目和有的大学的录取要求会略有不同。以下是通常的录取要求：","l老师和/或者升学指导的推荐信","lAP成绩和/或者SAT学科考试成绩","l 高中成绩单 l 升学指导推荐信 l SAT或ACT l高中成绩单 l老师推荐信 lSAT或者ACT l托福或者雅思 l高中成绩单 l目的陈述 lSAT或者ACT l托福或雅思 "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
GO
GO
