INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160129165732', N'Make unremitting efforts with a clear destination', N'1', N'Admin', N'2016-03-08 10:24:13.0000000', N'["\n\tVMA 2015-2016 Closing Ceremony \n","\n\n\tJanuary 28 was the last day of 2015-2016\nsemester. Right after the tense final examination, it came the first Vanke\nMeisha Academy (VMA) Closing Ceremony. We were glad to have four students of\nShenzhen Middle School (SMS) as our guests: Zhou Zixuan, Cao Jining, and Wang\nShangling brought their precious experience on preparation of college\napplication; Zhou Qianzi gave us a specific lecture of detailed strategies on\nTOEFL examination. All of the VMA teachers and students attended the ceremony\nand benefited a lot. At last, in the wonderful wishes from Executive Principal\nWang He, the first VMA closing ceremony concluded.\n","\n\n\tAfter the solemn flag-rising ritual, the closing\nceremony officially started. The first lecture was presented by SMS 2015\ngraduates Cao Jining and Zhou Zixuan, sharing their successful experience of\ncollege application. Cao Jining is now studying at Ecole Hoteliere Lausanne,\nSwitzerland. Zhou Zixuan is now a student of New York University. Their speech\nwas mainly about “make a clear destination” and “follow your interest to engage\ninto internships, co-curriculum activities, exchanges, and get to know the different\nuniversities”. They both suggested VMA students take earlier action to discover\ntheir own interests and passion, then conduct research about the major,\nuniversities through the internet and mass media. Zhou Zixuan emphasized many\ntimes that GPA is very important. They regretted that they did not study hard\nat the first and second year of high school, which resulted in the extremely\ntense accumulation of standard tests at the last year. Their simple but sincere\nwords made VMA students feel the time urgency to prepare for the standard\ntests.\n","\n\n\tThe second lecture was from Zhou Qianzi, who achieved\nthe high TOEFL score of 112. She focused her speech on the TOEFL tests,\nespecially the realistic learning strategies at the first year of high school. According\nto her, the goal should be set high: 100+ (more specific: Reading:27+, Listening:26+,\nSpeaking:22+, Writing: 25+). Secondly, students should pay attention to these\nnecessary materials: vocabulary book, TPO, Practice tests, and iBT TOEFL\nexperiences. She also listed some learning methods when referring to the\ndifferent particular examination contents. For the reading part, she strongly advised\nVMA students to recite a big amount of vocabulary, to analyze every difficult\nsentences, and to go through the TPO reading during the first year of high\nschool. She also gave suggestions on writing, speaking, and listening parts.\nThe lecture by Zhou Qianzi brought VMA students timely help, as they were on\ntheir way to their first try of TOEFL test during the winter vacation.\nTherefore, all the students took out paper and pen to record the important\npoints raised by Zhou Qianzi.\n","\n\n\tThe third lecture was from SMS current student\nWang Shangling, who has just received her early offer from The University of\nChicago. As the same as what the previous two lectures referred to, Wang\nShangling proposed that VMA students should begin the preparation earlier. She\ntended to correct students’ impression on vacation and pointed out that the\nvacation is not for hanging out, sleeping, or playing. It is for study, for a\nwhole plan for the coming semester, and for a precious time to fulfill your\nlearning objectives. Firstly, students should schedule all the test on their\ncalendar to show their current or long-term challenges. Among all the\nmotivations, personal interest is the best accompany and triggers for success.\nShe had been trying to apply for the famous international summer school in\nStanford although failed twice, but she never gave up. Her belief supported her\na lot, as she said, “As long as you work hard and be persistent, you can\napproach the success step by step. It may not be now, but the success will\ndefinitely be reached.” She then further proposed that students should grasp\nthe opportunities of conducting individual study at home during winter\nvacation: review the study of the last semester, make up for the deficiency,\nand make everyday a new progress. Her mother Ms Hu also gave advices for parents:\n“Actually, we could do a lot for our kids: monitor their study, help with the\nplanning, and cooperate with them. The most important thing is to communicate\nwith them.” Through Wang Shangling and her mother’s speeches, we firmly\nconcluded that there are a lot efforts waiting for both students and parents to\nmake on the way to success. Parents should try and explore students’ interest,\nsupport them, help them, assist them when facing the difficulties, and\naccompany them to the destination of success step by step.\n","\n\n\tThrough the three special lectures, Executive Principal\nWang He expressed her meaningful wishes: Make unremitting efforts with a clear destination.\nShe called on students to seize the coming winter vacation to achieve three\nimportant things: to explore your interest, passion and to set up your goal,\nspecifically, the university and the major you would choose to apply; to make\nshort-term and long-term plans；to strive to\naccomplish the plans step by step; and to cherish the wonderful moments of\nfamily time and contribute your love to your family, because this is what\nChinese spirits lies in.\n","\n\n\tIn 2015, we\nsowed the seeds of hope, and the harvest is abundant knowledge and great\nhappiness. When the spring of 2016 is approaching, the first VMA semester is\nmeeting its end successfully. We hope all the VMA students make use of the\nwinter vacation, make progress day by day, and face any opportunities and\nchallenges with the Meisha spirits in 2016! \n","\n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
GO
GO
INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160127151534', N'This is a School', N'2', N'Admin', N'2016-03-31 16:07:32.0000000', N'["\n\n\t\n\t\tThe speech of the first parents’ meeting of\nVanke Meisha Academy\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tby Wang Zhanbao, the Principal of Vanke\nMeisha Academy  the Principal of Shenzhen Middle School\n\t","\n\n\t\n\t\n\t\tEach\nperson, each environment, and each activity is relevant to ‘education’, and\neach of them is a journey. Today we have listened to the speeches presented by\nstudents, teachers, leaders of the academy, and especially our four parents. It\nis obvious that this is not an ordinary parents’ meeting, but a professional\none to share ---- because this is a school. I suggest you applaud to thank all\nthe parents, students and teachers who have participated in the sharing.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tStudents\nare going to spend three years in this newly-built school, so from 2015 to 2018\nthese three years, what will happen to our life and our home? How will our\nchildren be influenced by our families and our culture? I think, it is very\nnecessary to think about it before starting off.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThis is a school. It is neither a training\norganization, nor an overseas further education center.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, we must regard ‘educating people’ as the\nstarting point of everything.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tMeisha\nAcademy not only focuses on students’ academic work and further education, but\nalso pays attention to the growth of their moral character, will, mind, body\nand spirit ---- this kind of growth should not be didactic, monotonous, and\nenclosed, instead we hope for them to grow as well-rounded global citizen,\nfostered in a cross-cultural environment.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, we pay attention to not only children’s present,\nbut also their future. We need to lay a foundation for their deep learning, career development,\nand happy life within an international environment in the future.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, we definitely attach much importance to study\nand academics.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tOur\nschool’s motto is: Successful Future Through Creation. In the coming three\nyears, we will improve students’ academic standard by offering carefully\ndesigned courses, using developmental evaluation, participating in\ninternational high-end academic activities, establishing academic associations,\nand composing an academic thesis, and so on.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe\nwill carry out the inquiry learning around the idea of making the students of\nMeisha ‘study in a more valuable, freer, and more efficient way’. ‘Study in a\nmore valuable way’ means that study is based on the real needs of oneself, and\nchoices are closely relevant to one’s career planning.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\t‘Study\nin a freer way’ is firstly about ‘what to study’, which means study according\nto necessity instead of the things that you have already mastered. Study more\nabout things that you are interested, and deeply study things that need\nresearch. It also means conducting organized teaching according to students’\nbasis and needs, and endowing students the rights of initiating courses\nautonomously; Secondly, it is about ‘how to study’, which means apart from\nstudying in the regular way, learning by oneself, studying in advance, and\ngetting exemption for courses or classes that expand the way for obtaining\nacademic credit, and the experiences and abilities such as studying outside\nschool, studying online, and studying internationally can convert into academic\ncredit; Thirdly, it is about ‘when to study’, which means the learning process\ncan be selected and we can try a flexible educational system.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\t‘Study\nin a more efficient way’ includes flexible and dynamic course management and\nexecution methods, research-based teaching and learning, mentoring systems,\nstudents’ comprehensive quality evaluation scheme, and tools and techniques that\ncan make studying more efficient and in higher quality.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tPersonalized\nstudy becomes possible here. Our target is that ‘students study according to\ntheir needs, school offers education according to its needs, and colleges and\nuniversities select the talents according to their needs’. Moreover, as an\ninternational school with a mission, we must ‘take the whole world as our\ncampus, and enrich the educational recourses of the school’, and satisfy and\nimprove students’ need of personalized development. We should liberate students\nfrom idea to system, and let them spend their youth on more useful things, and\nmore necessary things for the future. We certainly should advocate ‘Hard Work\nPays Off’, but ‘hard work’ should be used at the developing points and should\nbe very worthy so that the youth will shine.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tOffering effective further education guidance for each student is the main\nidea of establishing this school.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe\nneed to pay attention to three core elements of admission to American\nuniversities. First is student’s academic standard, second is student’s\npersonality trait, and third is student’s academic potential.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe\nalso need to study the 2016 new reform proposal for SAT. In the new reform\nproposal, it not only shortens the original 2400 points into 1600 points, more\nimportantly, first, it emphasizes the study contents of students’ high school\ncourses; second, it emphasizes students’ abilities of analysis and application;\nthird, it emphasizes students’ ability of using evidence to answer questions;\nfourth, it emphasizes the abilities students need after entering universities.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe\nmust analyze all of these and must teach and learn effectively, so that the\nquality of our courses and teaching can be kept at a high level. Therefore,\nthere would be no surprises for the college entrance results of Vanke Meisha\nAcademy after three years due to the ideas, courses, teaching materials,\nactivities, associations, evaluations, teachers from home and abroad, and on tutors\nfrom Shenzhen Middle School.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, we take the students of the first session of\nthis new school as an opportunity of education, and as a course.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tIn\nPsychology, there is a term called ‘primacy effect’, also known as ‘first\nimpression effect’ or ‘advantage effect’. If there are several kids in a\nfamily, the eldest one will usually have something special compared to the\nyounger ones. For a school, the students of the first session will be the\nperpetually eldest ones and the seniors of the first session, will participate\nin the process of school’s creation and building, and will witness the\ndevelopment of a great school----this kind of developmental course is a\nlife-long educational resource itself.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThe\nstudents of the first session of a new school can be a challenge, can be a\nmemorable, can be family love, can be wealth, and can be resourceful, and this\nis the value of this special course. The Southwest Associated University of\nChina, the West Point of the U.S., and the Kian Kok Middle School of Taiwan all\nmake us feel this kind of value.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, the establishers have a lofty mission and heavy\nresponsibilities.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tAs for\nVanke Meisha Academy, the first semester is the most important. The\nestablishment of a school is different from any company, any social organization,\nor any Party and government organization. Why? These people are the future, are\nthe nation, are the world, and are humans.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThis\nis a school commissioned and established by Shenzhen Middle School. It is a new\nchallenge for Shenzhen Middle School as well. The international course system\nin Shenzhen Middle School has been set up for five years and has cultivated a\ngroup of brilliant students. Now Shenzhen Middle School cooperates with Vanke\nto establish an international high school together. Shenzhen Middle School will\ngo beyond history, to go beyond itself, to exploit a new way, to show the high\nquality and passion of China’s international high schools in this era of\nglobalization, to cultivate higher quality talents for our country and humans,\nto share our ideas, courses, evaluations, systems and cultures. It is a\nchallenge, but also a chance and an honor.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tBecause this is a school, we expect students, parents, teachers, and\nestablishers can be a community.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe expect parents to think about the three-year high school education from the perspectives\nof children’s life-long development and happy life; we expect you to respect\nthe profession of education, and understand and interact in a professional way;\nwe expect you to accompany, help, appreciate, and of course educate children\nwith us ---- but the education must be what the children need and must be\nappropriate.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe expect teachers to be knowledgeable and moral enough to be the role models. You are the\npractitioners of the school’s ethos, and your personal charisma and\nprofessional qualities should be impressive; you are both teachers and friends,\nyou guide students patiently and gently, you are mentors, and you are the pride\nof Meisha students; you have globalized perspective and international thought,\nand should use this kind of perspective and thought to carry out your education\nand teaching, and you should be students’ window for observing the world and\nbridging together with the new world.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe expect school establishers to take the mission, to have a broad and long view, to\nrespect the rules, to be courteous to the talents, to love the students as your\nchildren, and to have noble spirit, and we will be proud of you.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tEach\npart and each person should say, ‘I, am Vanke Meisha Academy!’\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThus,\nin three years, children, families, teachers will definitely have wonderful and\nunforgettable memories, and here will also become the port for a voyage, the\neternal memory and the source of happiness.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tVanke\nMeisha Academy is a school, which is built beside the South China Sea, moving\ntowards the world, and towards the future. The people fostered here have\nChinese people’s spirituality and energy. They are also the world’s citizens,\nand are the talents with leadership awareness and ability: this kind of talent\nis fostered with valuable and creative content, method, and environment.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThis, will be a school with excellent\nqualities.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tWe\nchoose this school. We will definitely create a future belonging to us.\n\t","\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n\n \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n \n\n\t  \n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
