INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160224213759', N'USAD: Challenge yourself in an international context', N'1', N'Admin', N'2016-04-27 10:53:37.0000000', N'["\n\t——A Glance at inner China Competition of USAD \n","\n\n\tFrom Feb. 19th to Feb. 21st, the inner China\ncompetition of 2016 United States Academic Decathlon (USAD) was held at the Futian\nShangri-La Shenzhen Hotel.USAD is one of the prime scholastic competition\nplatforms for teams of high school students in the US, has completed its 47th\nyear. Its main purpose is to provide a platform for students to demonstrate\ntheir knowledge and skills in ten different academic areas. The topics combine seven\nacademic subjects (Math, Science, Social Science, Economic, Literature, Music,\nand Art) and three inter-active subjects (Speech, Interview, Assessment\nContent-using team work and critical thinking skills), encouraging the candidates\nto learn from brand new perspectives and systems, in order to inspire students\nto develop new interests, enhance their performance at school, and to bridge\nconnections to their future college studies.\n","\n\n\tEach school participated in the\ncompetition as a school group, sending several teams to represent the school.\nTeams consist of nine students, from three different academic levels that they\nmust learn to work together. They attended the competition of talents and\nacademics. The nine students in each group were good at different subjects and\ncooperate with their specific strengths. All the teams were picked after strict\nselection through the layers of district-level, city-level, state-level, and\nfinally the nation level.\n","\n\n\tVanke Meisha Academy (VMA) was selected\nto join the inner China Competition. This year the competition topic is\n“India”. There were total\n37 participating schools，which sent out 86 teams. Vanke Meisha Academy\nsent out 4 teams, which consist of 39 students to attend the competition.\n","\n\n\tIn the morning of Feb. 19th, all\nthe contestants and coaches dressed formally and attended the opening ceremony.\nMany excellent students from Chinese top middle schools were ready to compete,\nfor instance, Shanghai Midddle School, Beijing No. 11 school, Middle school\nattached to SouthChina Normal University, and so on. Also, there were some students,\nwho had last year’s competition experience. As all the contestants entered the\nhall with their waving school flags, the atmosphere was extremely excited.  \n","\n\n\tThe competition started in the\nafternoon. The first round was the objective questions contest for Music,\nScience, Social science, Literature, Mathematics, and Economics. After super,\nthe most nervous test of Super\nQuiz started. All the students were so concentrated to answer the questions in\norder within seven seconds. They were trying to earn every score points for the\nteam. The rule of instant disclosure of correct answers allowed the students to\nread the situation progress. It was so touching. No matter what the team\nmembers’ performance turned out to be, when the team member returned to the\nteam, there was no complain or blame. All the team member encouraged and\npraised each other and fill everyone with positive energy.  \n","\n\n\tOn the second day of competition,\nit was the contests of synthesized test on Speech, Interview, and Accessment\nCenter. Accessment Center emphasize a lot on teamwork. The contestants need to use their strengths of Physics, Math,\nand other subjects to calculate. During the process, they still kept the\nconcepts of architectural mechanics and aesthetics design in mind. Finally,\neach team fulfilled these tasks that seemed to be impossible at the very\nbeginning.  \n","\n\n\tThe evening of Feb. 20 was the\nUSAD Gala Night. The shows and music added a lot of joy and happiness to the competition.\nVMA student Yan Yining, Ma Pingyi, Zhong Yantao, and Song Qingming gave wonderful\nperformance to all the audience and which earned the school thunderous applause.\nWhen it was near the end of the evening event, Yan yining was elected as the\nStar of USAD. As the only Chinese academic partner of USAD, VMA students\nintroduced the VMA teaching features to the audience. They also exhibited the\noriginal arts crafts by themselves and their humor and happy mood inspired many\nmeaningful communications.\n","\n\n\tIn the morning of Feb. 21st, it was the awards ceremony. VMA was awarded\nthe “Certificate of Appreciation”. For group award, VMA was the Team56\nAssessment Center (AC) Bronze Winner. We were honored to share that students\nalso won many individual awards: Literature Gold Winner (Yan Yining), Interview\nSilver Winner (Tang Ziying), Interview Bronze Winner (Wang Yufan), Essay Bronze\nWinner (Zhang Yuning), Speech Bronze Winner (Chen Jiayu, Liu Jiayu). The\nhighest scoring Decathlete from each team were: Mo Zhenming, Zhang Yuning, Yan\nYining, Wang Yulin. Especially Yan Yining was selected as “the Star of USAD”.\nAll the endeavors had fruitful outcomes and students were grateful for the\nencouragement and instruction from the school and teachers. \n","\n\n\tThe three days’ competition ended, students claimed： “UASD， see you next year!”. During the four months’ preparation, students have\ngained a lot in terms of critical ability, sense of teamwork, self-learning\nability, time management ability, courage to challenge. After they were back to\nschool, they reflected on the competition and learnt even more.  \n","\n\n\tP.S. Awards by Vanke Meisha Academy\n","\n\n\t\n\n\n\tIndividual\nawards: \n","\n\n\tEssay Bronze\nWinner: Zhang Yuning \n","\n\n\tLiterature\nGold Winner: Yan Yining \n","\n\n\tInterview\nBronze Winner: Wang Yufan \n","\n\n\tInterview\nSilver Winner:Tang Ziying \n","\n\n\tSpeech\nBronze Winner:Chen Jiayu \n","\n\n\tSpeech\nBronze Winner: Liu Jiayu \n","\n\n\tHighest Scoring\nDecathlete from each Team：Mo Zhengming,\nZhang Yuning, Yan Yining, Wang Yulin \n","\n\n\tGroup Awards： \n","\n\n\tTeam56\nAC(Assessment Center) Bronze Winner \n","\n\n\tCertificate\nof Appreciation \n","\n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t  \n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
