INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160128093353', N'Choose Vanke Meisha Academy to realize your brilliant future', N'1', N'Admin', N'2016-03-14 15:11:25.0000000', N'["\n\t—The 1st session of Teachers and\nParents Meeting of Vanke Meisha Academy was successfully held \n","\n\n\tOn the morning of August 16, 2015, the 1st session of Vanke Meisha Academy (VMA) Teachers\nand Parents Meeting was successfully held in the Qingyun Auditorium, Da Meisha,\nVanke Center. More than 900 parents gathered with their children to listen to\nthe wonderful introduction and presentation by the management team of VMA.\nAfter the meeting, the teaching and dormitory areas of the Academy were open\nfor visits. \n","\n\n\tThe two-hour meeting contains abundant\ninformation. In order to enable parents to better understand the incoming\nsenior high school life in the VMA and get well prepared for their children,\nthe school specially invited Ye Anlin, a student of International System of\nShenzhen Middle School in senior grade 3 to share her experience. Focusing on\nthe three courses that a student of International System must experience:\ndetermining goals, selecting methods, and contemplating one’s own future, she\nnarrated her feelings and thoughts to the public.\n","\n\n\tAfter the keynote speech by students, the\nemcee grandly introduced VMA organization structure. Under the effective and\npractical leadership of the administrative team, 23 Chinese and foreign\nteachers came to their debut. They are the first group of VMA teachers,\nincluding 17 Chinese teaching staff and 6 foreigners, who are recruited from\nglobal selection or recommended by Shenzhen Middle School. With broad\ninternational visions, fine education background, rich teaching and unique\nmanagement experience, they will work diligently at VMA to provide\ncomprehensive instructions in study, clubs, school life and enrollment for\nstudents. They will also become good tutors and friends in the course of\nstudents’ growth.\n","\n\n\tThen Academic\nPrincipal Gao Qing made a brief introduction to the the curriculum, which\nadvocates students’ comprehensive development, personal development and\nexcellent development. Especially the school came up with the layered education\ncurriculum system, which is composed of regular courses, honorary courses and\nprerequisite courses. Therefore, students can have a diversified choice among\nthese courses. In addition, the Academy practices cross-disciplinary teaching\nand credit offset systems, which enable every student to gain the opportunity\nto show themselves and develop their professions. Under the direction of the\noverall curriculum frame, teachers of different subjects further elaborated the\ncurriculum structure, academic activities, and international competition that related\nto the four fields - humanities, mathematics, English and natural sciences.\n","\n\n\tMeanwhile,\nthe Academy also attached great importance to students’ growth in terms of\nstudents’ life, extra-curriculum activities and other international resources\nand activities. The Assistant to director of Students Care Department, Li\nXianyao, gave a detailed introduction and innovatively expressed the\nconnotation of English abbreviation VMA for Vanke Meisha Academy, which means\neach student could acquire victory, leave memories, and make achievements!\n","\n\n\tVanke Meisha\nAcademy, as an internationalized senior high school jointly run by the Vanke\nEducation Development Fund and Shenzhen Middle School, has exceptional\neducation resources. It assigned excellent teachers from Shenzhen Middle School\nto be the instructors for each curriculum. And the instructors will closely\ncooperate with the teachers of the Academy to carry out teaching research and\npractice. Host introduced the achievements and experience of the instructors\nfrom Shenzhen Middle School in detail to the students and their parents.\nPrincipal Wang Zhanbao also enacted the Letter of Engagement for the\ninstructors, symbolizing the academic cooperation between Shenzhen Middle\nSchool and Vanke Meisha Academy will carry out closely and permanently.\n","\n\n\tDuring\nthe process of children’s growth, the education from schools, families and\nsociety play important roles. To promote the connection between the family and\nschool, the Academy established an education community including teachers,\nparents and their social communities. Especially the Academy invited four\nparents (two of them are the members of the Parents Committee of Shenzhen\nMiddle School), whose children once studied and are studying in the\nInternational System of Shenzhen Middle School, to share their understanding\nand thoughts in terms of school cooperation, rights and responsibilities of the\nParents Committee, and family education. Zhou Qingyang’ s mother, also the\ndirector of the Parents Committee of Shenzhen Middle School in senior grade 3,\nexpounded the connotations of parents as the school and teachers’ consultants\nand assistants, and put forward the principle of “Three Needs and Three Not’s”\nfor the committee work, i.e., not exceed one’s authority, not take everything\non one’s own, not blindly follow; need communication, need understanding, and\nneed forgiveness. These are the bonds to establish mutual trust between\nfamilies and school, but also the communication bridge. Although they are\ndifferent families, they had similar happy stories, which stems from the\nparents’ appropriate help and giving freedom to their children, stems from\ntrusting the innovative courses and grading education, and stems from the\nunderstanding and support to the school education. Let’s expect the tacit\nunderstanding and affection between the families and school to begin from Vanke\nMeisha Academy in September.\n","\n\n\tAt the\nend of the meeting, principal Wang Zhanbao made the conclusion. He pointed out\nthat the first three years are very critical for Vanke Meisha Academy to train\nits first group of students, for its full of innovation and surpassing\nopportunities. To surpass the opportunities, we have to rely on our unique\nholistic education system, caring more about students’ comprehensive growth\nthan their pure academic performance, and valuing more students’ future than\ntoday. Meisha Academy will seize the opportunity and meet challenges from its\nfirst step, so as to create unique memories for the struggling teachers and\nstudents here. Vanke Meisha Academy will become the place where they can\nharvest friendship, taste the successful pleasure, and turn the three years of\nexperience into their wealth of life to reward the permanent resources\naccumulated by the Academy. With students’ demand as the direction and through\npersonalized education for actual needs, Meisha Academy shall help students to\ninternalize the core elements for college enrollment, and care about students’\ncomprehensive development including their morals, academic thinking and social\nability, so as to cultivate them towards the next generation that insist on\nlifelong study, serve, and lead the society. We are sure that is the future\nVanke Meisha Academy shall create.\n","\nFinally, the 1st session of Teachers and\nParents Meeting of Vanke Meisha Academy came to a successful end. After the\nmeeting, parents still chatted with teachers in the consultation area. And they\nalso experienced the facilities and equipment in the teaching and residential\nareas under the direction of the working staff. They all burst into smiles.\nChoosing this school to study from 2015 to 2018, the students will be bound to\ncreate their beautiful future!\n","\n\n\tYe Anlin, student of International System\nof Shenzhen Middle School, senior grade 3, shared her thoughts. \n","\n\n\tParents and teachers carefully\nlistened to the speech and burst with heated applauses. \n","\n\n\tAcademic Principal Gao Qing of Vanke Meisha\nAcademy introduced the Academy’s overall curriculum design system.\n","\n\n\tRepresentative teacher Wu\nNingxin, Chinese teacher of Vanke Meisha Academy introduced the humanities curriculumsystem\n","\n\n\tTeacher representative Marco\nof English Department of Vanke Meisha Academy introduced English curriculum. \n","\n\n\tTeacher representative Chen Shaorui of the Physics group of Vanke Meisha Academy introduced natural\nsciences curriculum system. \n","\n\n\tAssistant to Director of Students Care\nDepartment Li Xianyao introduced student associations, school life,\ninternational competitions and resources arrangement in details. \n","\n\n\tPrincipal Wang Zhanbao of Vanke Meisha\nAcademy presented awards Letter of Engagement to instructors from Shenzhen\nMiddle School and had a group photo with them.\n","\n\n\tInstructor Luo Zhiwen, head of\nhistory group of Shenzhen Middle School gave a speech. \n","\n\n\tPrincipal Wang Zhanbao of\nVanke Meisha Academy delivered a speech. \n","\n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n \n\n\t  \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t\n \n\n\t  \n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
