INSERT INTO [dbo].[articals] ([id], [title], [contenttype], [author], [publishtime], [content], [content-img], [content-img-trans]) VALUES (N'20160203130312', N'Vanke Meisha Academy Launch Ceremony & Commission Conference', N'1', N'Admin', N'2016-03-14 10:56:33.0000000', N'["\n\t\n\t\tCooperative Education between Vanke Meisha\nAcademy and Shenzhen Middle School\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tOn\nJune 13 2015, Vanke Education Development Fund held the “Vanke Meisha Academy\nLaunch Ceremony  Commission Conference of Cooperative Education with\nShenzhen Middle School” at Vanke Center, Qianhai, Shenzhen. Vice Mayor Wu\nYihuan, Director of Education Bureau Guo Yurong, Vanke President Yu Liang,\nVanke Vice President and manager Zhou Tong, and the Principal of Shenzhen\nMiddle School Wang Zhanbao attended the conference. More than 600 parents and\nstudents presented there and the atmosphere was full of excitement and joy.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThe\nVanke Vice President and manager Zhou Tong was the first speaker, he stated\nthat Vanke has accumulated more than 30 years’ experience and is now trying to\nconduct transition strategy of “city supporting service provider”. Vanke will\nnot only engage with property service, but also with the construction and\ndevelopment of business, education, provision for the aged, culture, and other\nfields. “Education always goes the first”. Vanke President Yu Liang, Vanke Vice\nPresident and manager Zhou Tong, Chairman of Vanke Education Development Fund\nTang Lu, Principal of Shenzhen Middle School Wang Zhanbao, Vice Principal Xing\nXiangzhao, and Assistant to Principal Gao Qing raised the sail together, which was\nsymbolic of the launch of Vanke Meisha Academy. Right after that, the both\nsides signed the agreement on the Cooperative Education with Shenzhen Middle\nSchool. The both side will work together to build one of the top international\nschools. Vanke President Wang Shi and the honor Principal of Vanke Meisha\nAcademy, who is now studying at Cambridge University, also sent his hope and\nwishes.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tPrincipal\nWang Zhanbao expressed his respects and appreciation for the responsibility\nthat Vanke agreed to shoulder. It followed by his speech on Chinese students\nwho are now studying abroad. He summarized the current status of going abroad: agency\nreplaced school, foreigner replaced teachers, partners replaced parents, and USA\nreplaced world.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tHe\nthen introduced that some of the most important ability and skill that VMA would\nequip its students: VMA is going to cultivate global citizens and leaders with\nChinese identity. VMA students will be equipped with academic skills, critical\nthinking, problem-solving ability, sense of self-conscious, communicative\nability, and social practice. VMA will be the start point that Shenzhen Middle\nSchool going international. The speech inspired everybody and won an\never-lasting applause.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tAt\nlast, Vanke President Yu Liang presented his excellent speech. He referred to\nthat Shenzhen has ranked No. 1 in China in aspect of economy. “However, there\nis still space for the development of education and medical service, which\nactually hindered the progress and development of the city. As a responsible\nenterprise, Vanke has been pondering over the ideal and actual strength to build\na good school. And we believe that we are going to cultivate excellent students\nthrough joint efforts with Shenzhen Middle School, which is a famous school\nwith actual strength.”\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tDuring\nthe school information session, Principal Wang Zhanbao leaded the whole VMA\nmanagement team to give introduction of VMA. He emphasized the educational\nmission of VMA is to cultivate global citizens and leaders with Chinese\nidentity. All the teaching resource and curriculum must focus on this. Then the\nquestion is how to realize it? The VMA motto answered this question: Successful\nFuture through Creation. All the teaching work must focus on the two keys.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tLater\non, Academic Principal Gao Qing illustrated VMA curriculum.It is designed\nbased on the structure of the International Baccalaureate (commonly known as “IB”)\nprogram. The courses range from the conventional standards to subjects\noffered at leading and progressive American high schools. We embrace diversity\namong our students and faculty, in reference to their opinions, attitudes, cultures\nand traditions. The educational experiences we provide promotes the\ndevelopment of individual characteristics of each student. The three\ntypes of creative courses designed with the rich and profound concepts of of\neducation constitute the novel VMA international school courses. In addition to\nstimulating intellectual growth and passing on academic knowledge, we also\nstrive to prepare our students for future to tackle challenges by employing\ntheir individual strengths and aptitudes.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tAt\nlast, Executive Principal Wang He presented a general introduction and answered\nthe concerned questions from the perspectives of admission and school\nmanagement.\n\t","\n\t\n\t\tThis ceremony is a landmark for the cooperation\nof Vanke and Shenzhen Middle School. With the strengths from both side, we are\ngoing to build one of the top international school to repay our school, our\ncity, our time!\n\t\n","\n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\t\n\t\t\n\t \n\n\t\n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\t \n \n\n\n\t  \n \n\n\n\t  \n \n\n\n\t  \n \n\n\t  \n "]', N'[""]', N'[""]')
